  "text": "The upstream connection pool overflow condition in Envoy is defined and handled across multiple C++ source files:\n\n**Overflow State Definition:**\nThe overflow state is defined as the `PoolFailureReason::Overflow` enum value in `envoy/common/conn_pool.h` (lines 96-105). This enum represents a condition where a resource has overflowed and policy prevented a new connection from being created.\n\n**Overflow Handling and Emission:**\n\n1. **Connection-level overflow (upstream_cx_overflow)**: In `source/common/conn_pool/conn_pool_base.cc`, the `tryCreateNewConnections()` method at line 138 increments the `upstream_cx_overflow` counter when `host_->canCreateConnection(priority_)` returns false, indicating the connection creation limit has been reached.\n\n2. **Stream-level overflow (upstream_rq_pending_overflow)**: In `source/common/conn_pool/conn_pool_base.cc`, the `attachStreamToClient()` method at line 179 handles the case when max concurrent streams are exceeded and calls `onPoolFailure()` with `PoolFailureReason::Overflow`. Additionally, the `newStreamImpl()` method at line 286 handles pending request overflow when `host_->cluster().resourceManager(priority_).pendingRequests().canCreate()` returns false.\n\n3. **Connection pool-level overflow (upstream_cx_pool_overflow)**: In `source/common/upstream/conn_pool_map_impl.h`, the `getPool()` template method at line 38 increments the `upstream_cx_pool_overflow` counter when the connection pool resource limit is reached and cannot free an existing pool.\n\n**Statistics Definition:**\nThe statistics counters are defined in `envoy/upstream/upstream.h` (lines 731, 732, 748):\n- `upstream_cx_overflow`: Incremented when a new connection cannot be created due to policy limits\n- `upstream_cx_pool_overflow`: Incremented when a new connection pool cannot be created due to resource limits\n- `upstream_rq_pending_overflow`: Incremented when pending request queue or max concurrent streams are exceeded\n\n**Implementation Flow:**\nThe connection pool implementation in `source/common/conn_pool/conn_pool_base.cc` (class `ConnPoolImplBase`) orchestrates the overflow handling: when `newStreamImpl()` is called, it either finds an available connection and calls `attachStreamToClient()`, or queues the request as a pending stream. During attachment, if resource limits are exceeded, the stream is failed with `PoolFailureReason::Overflow` and the appropriate counter is incremented."
}

